inn1.comm: Mills starts off with a beauty, seamed away after pitching on off, had Haddin feeling for that one
good length outside off and moving away a touch, left alone to the keeper
getting the ball to jag away from the batsman after pitching on a length, Clarke gets confidently on the front foot and defends
this time it full on the pads, Clarke nudges it towards mid-on
good over so far from Mills, again keeping it tight around the offstump, defended to midwicket off the back foot
good length again, draws Clarke onto the front foot, he taps it towards extra cover
he follows the Mills model, back of a length on offstump, Haddin watchfully defends it off the backfoot
defended to mid-on off the backfoot
Southee strays onto middle and leg this time, Haddin punches it wide of mid-on for a single
reverts to pitching it up, giving the batsman no room to work with, Clarke defends it back to the bowler
yorker this time on middle and off, Clarke squeezes it out back to the bowler
length ball about a foot outside off, Clarke shoulders arms to that one
that was a length ball, but Haddi is happy to play it off the backfoot, he opens the face of the bat to play it towards point
a touch wide outside off, nice length though, drawing Haddin onto the front foot, but the batsman opts against offering a stroke at the last moment
this time it is speared into legstump, Haddin just about get some bat on it, inside edge on the pads and the ball rolls towards square leg
this time it is stabbed towards point, no run as it goes straight to the bowler
overpitched on middle and leg, Clarke helps himself to a couple by driving it wide off mid-on
short and wide, Clarke thrashes it towards point, can't beat the fielder there though
driven with soft hands towards mid-off, no run
this time it's on middle stump, Haddin was looking to hammer that through midwicket, gets an inside edge onto his pads
back of a length and angling into the batsman, Haddin backs away and wants to clobber it down the ground, but he mistimes it to the bowler
stabbed towards backward point, a much more controlled shot this time, placement was awary again
pitched up, Haddin crashes it towards mid-off, where Vettori puts in a full length dive to his left to cut off the ball
blocked back to the bowler
that was coming, just a fraction full, he charges down the track and lofts it over mid-on
short of a length on the off stump, mistimes a pull wide of square leg for a single
erring in length here and Australia are finally getting a move-on, short on middle, rocks back and pulls it away over midwicket for a boundary
good length on the off stump, gets forward and defends it to short cover
poor ball, fine leg was up and Mills pays the price, full on the pads, Clarke glaces it to the fine-leg boundary
short of a good length on the off stump, guided wide of point for a single
short of a good length outside off, gets forward and drive it crisply through the covers, was not quite to the pitch there but played through the line to get three runs
slower ball bowled short outside off, makes room and chops it to point
short of a good length on middle, defended back to the bowler
short of a good length outside off, makes room and slices it away over the covers for three more
,good length on the leg stump, tries to work it it away wide of midwicket, gets a leading edge just wide of Peter Fulton at short cover. He could have caught that, but was really slow to react
short of a length on middle, defended off the back foot into the off side
short on the off stump, makes room, opens the face and guides it to third man for a single
short on the off again, pushed firmly off the back foot wide of cover for a single
slower  ball on middle and leg, defended watchfully towards mid-on
short on middle and off again, defended comfortably off the back foot towards point

slower one again, would have been close had the throw been accurate, pushed away into the leg side and they try to come back for the second, a wayward throw from square leg gives the ample time to get back
slower one again, cut away to point, need to bowl much fuller here
short of a good length on the off stump, pushed to midwicket off the back foot
hit through the line there, bowled on a good length outside off, no movement on that one, lofted over mid-off for a boundary
short of a good length outside off, slashed away to point
slower ball bowled full on the off stump, pushed off the front foot to cover, decides against the single
short on middle, comes down the track and pulls it away towards deep midwicket
on middle and leg, tries to flick it away towards square leg, gets an inside edge onto the pads
slower ball bowled outside off, keeps really low, Clarke fails to get his bat down in time
pushed away off the front foot to midwicket
turned away off the front foot towards deep square leg, again a touch too short
short of a length outside off, guided off the back foot to third man
on a good length on the off stump, pushed firmly back to the bowler
short of a good length on the off stump, comes forward and closes the face to push it wide of midwicket for a single
short of a good length on middle and off, pushed to midwicket
full on middle and off, driven firmly back to the bowler
short outside off, missed opportunity there, cut away towards cover where a fumble allows them a run
misfield again, not quite to the pitch there, on a good length on the off stump, mistimes a slog to Elliot at mid-on who lets the ball go through his legs to allow the batsmen a couple
a couple more, mistimed again but still effective, good length on the off stump, strikes it uppishly just slightly over mid-off
short of a good length on middle and off, pushed back past the bowler towards mid-on for a single
slower ball bowled full outside off, driven off the front foot to mid-off who's standing at the edge of the circle
short on middle, pulled away wide of deep square leg for a couple
slower ball on the off stump, pushed to mid-off for a single
slower one again, short on the off stump, run down to third man for a single

we have an injury here, hopefully just a minor one, spat off the pitch, short of a good length outside off, Haddin missed an upper-cut towards third man, and McCullum was struck hard on the shoulders. He's understandably in a bit of pain there, and the players take a short break while he receives some medical attention
short of a good length outside off, pushed off the back foot to cover. 50 up for Australia, at a healthy rate
drifting into the right hander from round the wicket, pushed through quick, tries to work it away on the leg side, gets a thick outside edge
shorter on middle and off, pushed back to the bowler
quicker ball on middle and leg, played away to midwicket
short of a length outside off, cut away to deep cover off the back foot
tossed up on leg stump, driven to midwicket
short and wide, cut away to deep cover again
full on the off stump, driven back to the bowler off the front foot
short of a length on the off stump, mistimes a pull straight to midwicket
short outside off, faild to get the deserved treatment as there's cover in the deep, cut away fiercely
full on the off stump, driven wide of mid-off off the front foot for a single
short of  length outside off, much slower through the air there, chopped down to point and they decide against the single
yorker outside off, tries to driven through the line, gets an edge all along the ground to the keeper
short of a length outside off, cut away powerfully wide of deep cover for a couple
beautifully timed, flighted on the off stump, charges down the track and lofts it cleanly over mid-off for a boundary
tossed up on middle and leg, driven through the line all along the ground to long-on
short outside off, cut away to cover
flighted on middle and leg, down the track and driven to mid-off
much slower through the air on middle and leg, defended on the on-side
good length outside off, driven firmly to mid-off
short of a good length outside off, jagged back in a touch, pushed wide of midwicket for a quick single
low full toss on the off stump, pushed wide of the bowler for a single to mid-off
short of a length outside off, slashed away off the back foot to third man
poor ball, but gets away with it, short and wide, Haddin mistimes a cut straight to point
good length outside off, driven uppishly wide of cover for a single
tossed up, pitches outside leg stump, he comes down the track and pads it away
big one, in the slot for Haddin, full on middle, there's plenty of air on that one, Haddin gets down on one knee and slogs-sweeps it over the deep midwicket boundary for a massive six
tossed up on middle and off, driven off the front foot to mid-off
tossed up on middle and leg. pushed off the front foot to long-on
short of a length outside off, cut to short cover
on middle and leg, driven to midwicket
lucky, good length on middle and leg, tries to slog it away over midwicket, gets a thick inside edge just wide of the leg stump to the fine-leg boundary
full and gets the treatment, stays his ground and lofts it cleanly over mid-on for a one bounce four
short of a good length on middle, punched off the back foot to long-on
short of a good length on middle and leg, pushed off the back foot to midwicket
short of a length outside off, nipped back in sharply, Clarke tried ti cut that past point but was surprised by the bounce and inward movement
full on middle and leg, driven off the front foot wide of mid-on for a single
tossed up on middle and leg, driven down the ground to long-on
shot! Flighted on middle and off, gets to the pitch by coming down the tracn and driving it firmly back past the bowler to evade long-on to the boundary
short on middle and off, pushed off the back foot to long-off
down the track and driven firmly to long-on
flighted outside off stump, eased through the off side to deep cover
short of a length on middle, rocks back and pulls it away to deep midwicket
full on the off stump, driven on the up, falls short of mid-off
short of a good length outside off, guided to point off the back foot
there it is, full on middle and leg, driven off the front foot comfortably to long-on. Brings up his sixth ODO half-century
short and wide, cut away to deep point
short of a length outside off, cut off the back foot to third man

excellent batting, bowled short of a good length on midd;e, he strikes the ball through the line well over mid-on for a boundary. He is timing the ball beautifull here and getting the distance despite not coming to the pitch
short of a length outside off, chases it from the crease, the ball swings away at the last moment to miss the outside edge
slower through the air, bowled on a good length outside off, Haddin failed to pick and and just chipped it over Daniel Vettori at mid-off for a couple
full on middle and off, driven back to the bowler
on a good length on the off stump, defended off the back foot
in the slot for Haddin there, a hapless slower delivery bowled full on middle and leg, he gets down on one knee and plays a lofted sweep well wide of deep square leg for another big one
short of a length on middle and off, pushed to mid-on
flighted on middle, charges down the wicket to smash it over the bowlers head for a huge six. Gets to his 32nd fifty
dropped, short of a length outside off, tries to late cut it in the third-man region, gets a thick outside edge that McCullum gets his glove to but fails to pouch
flighted on middle and leg, driven down the ground to long-on
pushed off the front foot through midwicket for a single
flighted on middle and off, driven down the ground to long-on
full on middle and leg, pushed off the front foot to long-on
short of a good length on the off stump, pushed off the back foot to cover
short of a length on the off again, hit to the same fielder albeit a little more firmly
slower ball bowled on a good length on middle and leg, pushed through the line to mid-on
short on middle and leg, flicked away off the back foot to fine leg
picked up the slower one there, NZ have bowled way too many of them tooday, full on the off stump, slogged away over midwicket for a boundary. The runs continue to flow
full on middle and leg, driven to midwicket where a fumble allows them a single. New Zealand losing their guard here
flighted on middle and off, down the track and flicks it away to deep midwicket
tossed up on middle, defended watchfully on the leg side
pushed through quicker this time, good length on the off stump, defended
superb fielding by Elliot, tossed up on middle, swept away powerfully wide of deep square leg where Elliot dives full length to cut that off just inside the ropes
flighted on middle and leg, driven to long-on
short of a length on middle and leg, pushed away off the back foot to deep midwicket
struck on the wrong spot there, short on middle and leg, tries to pull it away over midwicket, misses and he's brave enough to not show he's in pain
short outside off, cut away to deep point
wide down the leg side but brilliantly kept by McCullum

slower one bowled full outside off, Clarke makes room and drives it powerfullu but straight to Martin Guptill at short cover. Finally a wicket but not after an excellent start by the Australian openers
slower ball bowled short outside off, cut away to point
off the mark, short of a length outside off, guided off the back foot third man
short of a length on middle and leg, tries to turn it away fine, is s truck high on the pads
tossed up on the off stump, defended off the front foot to point
flighted on middle, pushed back to the bowler
there are just three fielders in the deep, bowled short outside off and spinning into Ponting, gets on the back foot and punches it through the covers for a boundary
flighted outside off, driven back to the bowler
on middle and leg, flicked away to deep square leg
short of a good length on the off stump, no spin on that one, eased through the midwicket region for a single
good length on the off stump, pushed back to the bowler
slightly short on middle and leg, pushed to midwicket
slower offcutter bowled on a good length outside off, guided to third man for a single
short of a length outside off, cut away to point
good length on the off stump, defended off the front foot to cover
short of a good length outside off, punched off the back foot to cover
tossed up on middle and off, driven to long-off
flighted on leg stump, driven gently wide of long-on, plenty of open spaces, they get a couple
almost! Short of a length outside off, unexpected bounce there, kicks off the pitch and Haddin struggles to keep it down as it stops him, dabbed uppishly wide of cover
tossed up on middle and off, eased through the cover region
flighted on leg stump, driven down the ground to long-on
short of a length outside off, guided off the back foot wide of point for a single
slower ball bowled short on the off stump, pushed to mid-on
The mid-on fielder has been pushed back now and they get a single in the same region
on middle and leg, pushed off the back foot to long-on

dropped, slower ball bowled full on middle and off, lofts it really high wide of Peter Fulton at long-on who puts down an easy chance. He ran a few steps backwards to his right, got into a good position, but spilled it sight at the last moment, deflecting the ball to the boundary
pushed off the back foot to the bowler
on middle and leg, drive to mid-on
flighted on the off stump, punched off the back foot to deep cover
flighted on middle and off, defended on the leg side
tossed up on middle and leg, pushed back to the bowler
tossed up on the off stump, pushed off the front foot to cover
good over so far, drives a flighted ball back to the bowler
on middle and leg, driven off the front foot to midwicket. Just one of the over
slower ball on leg stump, worked away off the front really fine, wide of Mills at fine-leg for three runs
short of a length on middle, pulled away to deep midwicket
short on middle and leg, flicked away to deep square leg
yorker length outside off, reaches out and digs it out to cover
shot! Fractionally full outside off, gets forward and drives it well over cover for a boundary
good length on middle and leg, turned away neatly to deep square leg
short of a length outside off, chopped down to deep cover off the back foot
flighted on the off stump, driven to cover
flighted on the off stump, dropped on the off side , decide against the single
on the off stump, guided off the front foot to point
bowled flatter on the off stump, pushed off the front foot to cover
tossed up on middle and off, driven gently to cover. The end of another good over from Vettori
short of a good length on leg stump, pushed off the back foot to midwicket
short outside off, makes room and thrashes that down to deep cover

top-edge and excellent catch at fine-leg by Mills, short of a length on middle and off, tries to pull it away over square leg, gets the leading edge and Mills, despite the sun being being in his eyes, pouches it superbly
slower ball bowled full on middle and off, driven off the front foot to mid-off
short of a good length outside, punched off the back foot to long-off
shot! Full outside off and he just chips it away over mid-off for a boundary. David Hussey off to a good start here
low full toss on middle and leg, driven to long-on, Haddin into the 90's now
flighted on leg stump, leans into the drive and plays it to long-on
short of a good length outside off, charges forward and defends it to the off side

Haddin is looking in great form here, tossed up on middle and leg, inviting the batsman to charge forward, lofts it cleanly over long-on for a big six. No sign of nerves here in the nineties for Haddin
almost gets it, tossed up outside off, he makes room and plays it inside-out over cover for a couple, Southee dives well to his left to prevent a certain four
full on middle and off, driven back to the bowler
Short of a good length on the off stump, tries to punch it off the back foot wide of the bowler, gets a thick outside edge wide of a diving point for  a single
short on middle and off, pushed to mid-off, moves to 99
flicked away wide of midwicket
good length on middle and off, defended back to the bowler
eased through the leg side to give Haddin the strike
full on middle and off, pushed back to the bowler. Haddin will have to wait till the next over

edged and gone! The bowling change works wonders. Short of a good length outside off and a hint of away movement and some sharp bounce, tries to run it down to third man, gets a thick outside edge that's snapped up comfortably by McCullum. Important breakthrough there, Hussey was looking good
short of a good length on middle and off, defended off the back foot
beaten by the sharp swing into him, good length on the off stump and jagged back in, White was struck in the mid-riff while trying to work it away wide of midwicket
short of a length outside off, guided off the back foot to point
short on middle, defended off the back foot to the bowler
short of a length outside off, pushed to point, maiden over
gets his maiden ODI century, short outside off, punches it wide of point for a single. Entertaining knock there, off just 107 balls, laced with three sixes
full outside off, gets a thick outside edge to third man as he tries to drive that through cover
slower ball bowled full outside off, makes room and slices that away to deep cover
fell safely there, bowled short on the off stump, tried to pull it towards deep midwicket, mistimes it, it lobs up in the air well short of Jeetan Patel
short of a good length outside off, pushed off the back foot to cover
slower ball on middle, reaches forward and chip it between long-on and deep midwicket for a couple
good length on middle and leg, driven straight to mid-on
tucked away wide of midwicket this time for a single
yorker outside off, tries to dig out from the crease, fails to bring his bat dow in time
full outside off, makes room and square drives it powerfully wide of point for a boundary
short of a length outside off, chopped away towards third man
good length outside off and swinging away a touch, left alone to the keeper
full on middle and leg, driven wide of mid-on for a single, it brings up the 200

run out, yorker length on middle, dug out awkwardly and Haddin storms down the pitch for a quick single, the ball rolls to McCullum who dives forward to throw down the stumps at the strikers end, to find Haddin well short of his ground. End of a superlative century from Haddin, but the middle-order now needs to step up with some quick runs
short of a good length outside off, pushed wide of cover for a quick single
full down the leg side, tries to glance it down fine, misses
full toss on middle and leg, punched down the ground to long-on
good length on middle and off, dropped on the off side and they scamper a quick single
yorker length outside leg, dug out wide of midwicket for a single
short on the off stump, pushed wide of cover for a quick single
short of a length outside off, cut away smartly to third man
bouncer banged in short outside leg, too high there and given a wide
White finally gets a boundary, he was kept quite until now, but that was banged in short outside off and he pulls it away powerfully wide of deep midwicket for a boundary

poor shot, bowled on a good length on the off stump, he goes for a blind loft over mid-off, mistimes it completely, gets a lot of elevation on it, Vettori takes a couple of steps back and takes a well-judged catch
how did that miss, short of a good length outside off, tries to run it down to third man, gets an inside edge over middle stump to the fine-leg boundary
good running there, worked away between deep square leg and fine leg for a couple
short of a length outside off and jagged back, guided to point off the back foot
slower ball bowled full outside off, driven firmly to mid-off
shot! Short of a length outside off, cut away over point wide of a diving third man for a pressure-relieving boundary
too straight, on middle and leg, whipped away off the pads to deep square leg
slower ball on leg stump, turned away to square leg for a single
short outside of, held its line, slashed at it off the back foot, missed
good length outside off, driven uppishly off the front foot to mid-off
on middle and leg, flicked away to deep square leg
short on middle, gets on the back foot and pulls it away over midwicket for a boundary
and again, slower ball, a rank long hop on leg stump, Hussey rocks on the back foot and helps it on its way to the fine-leg boundary
low full toss on the off stump, eased through the covers for a single
slower ball bowled short of a good length outside off, pushed off the back foot to cover
yorker length on middle, flicked away to deep square leg
shot! Full on the off stump, makes room and slices it away wide of point, beautifully timed, picked the length perfectly
full on middle and leg, walks across and works it away wide of deeep square leg for a couple
slower ball bowled short of a length outside off, run down to third man
short of a length on middle and off, mistimes a pull wide of midwicket
good length on middle, makes room and chops it wide of point for a single
short of a length on the off stump, worked away off the back foot to deep square leg
short outside off, cut away wide of third man, he rushes back for the second, and despite an accurate throw, makes it comfortably
good length outside off, comes down the track and drives it crisply to cover, who misfields to allow the batsmen a single
poor ball, short on middle, he pulls it away fiercely wide of midwicket for a boundary
short of a good length outside off, opens the face to guide it wide of point for a quick single
Australia are going great guns here, slower ball bowled full outside off, he makes room and slices it over the two gully's stationed on the off side for a boundary
quicker one bowled short on the off stump, cut away to point
fired in quick again, on middle and off, defended off the back foot
short of a length outside off, cut well but straight to the point fielder
drifting into the right hander from round the wicket, steered wide of point for a single
much slower through the air, flighted on a good length outside off, tries to drive it to cover, misses
flighted on the off stump, lands full, opens the face to play it wide of point for a quick single
good length on middle and off, comes down the track and turns it away wide of midwicket for a single
full toss on leg stump, driven all along the ground to long-off
full on middle and leg, driven down the ground to long-on
full and down the leg side, tries to glance it down fine, McCullum fumbles it, given a bye
full outside off, driven through the off side, wide of cover for a single
poor ball, full on the pads with fine-leg up, flicked away really to beat the fielder there to the boundary
short on middle, turned away off the back foot wide of deep square leg to come back for a well run two. Lots of open spaces in the deep on the leg side
tossed up on middle and off, slogged away to deep square leg for a single
short of a length outside off, comes on really slow to the batsman, walks across and paddles it wide of fine-leg for two more

plumb in front! Tossed up on middle, bowled really slow at 78 kmph, he is into the sweep shot really early, is done is by the pace, strikes him on the back leg on line with the stumps and Bucknor makes a straightforward decision
driven towards short cover
driven off the front foot to long-on
low full toss on leg stump, driven straight to midwicket
slower ball bowled short outside off, tries to cut that away, but is into the shot too early, misses
good length outside off, driven on the up to long-off
full toss on middle and leg this time, flicked away from the crease to deep midwicket
low full toss on middle, makes room and drives it down the ground to long-off
slower ball bowled short on middle and leg, pulled away to deep square leg
full outside off, tries to drive it through the covers, gets a thick inside edge wide of square leg for a single
full outside off, slogged away to long-on
tight bowling here, almost yorker length outside off, squeezed through to cover
an attempted inswinging yorker on middle and leg, driven all along the ground for a single to long-on
good length outside off, makes room and strikes it firmly to deep cover
full outside off, driven to long-off, it takes a while to reach the fielder who's a touch too deep and they scramble back for the second
short of a length on middle and Hussey lashes on to that one, pulled away powerfully to the deep square leg boundary
almost had him lbw there, full on middle and off, tries to swing that away over short fine, gets a thin inside edge onto his pads
yorker length outside off, dragged away wide of midwicket for a single
shot! Low full toss on middle, bends just a touch and lofts it between deep midwicket and long-on for a boundary. 50 for Hussey, a very timely one, scored off just 30 balls
full on middle and leg, driven wide of midwicket for a single
full and straight, and it's timber! Yorker length on middle, Hopes makes room to slice that over point, misses it completely and hears the death rattle behind him

Hussey holes out in the deep, slower ball bowled full on middle and leg, he gets forward and slogs it straight to Ross Taylor at deep midwicket. End of a cruical innings after the openers had given the hosts a sound start
slower ball bowled on a good length on off stump, driven down the ground to long-off
dropped, good length on the off stump, driven back past the bowler who gets a hand but deflects it to long-off. That was firmly struck, and though catchable, was a really sharp chance

300 up! Low full toss on leg stump, driven back past the bowler who fumbles to allow the batsmen to come back for two. However, the batsmen were warned there for running on the danger area of the wicket for the second time, and therefore the runs have been negated
gone! Slower ball on middle and leg, slogged away straight to Jeetan Patel at deep midwicket.
full outside off, driven off the front foot to long-off, the fielder there returns a wayward throw to McCullum to allow the batsmen to come back for the second and go past 300

inn2.comm: runs straightaway, short of a length on middle and leg, pushed away wide of midwicket for a single
good length outside off and moving away, left alone
good length on middle and off, driven off the front foot to m,id-off
beaten, good length outside off and leaving the right hander, prods at it off the back foot, clips the pads on the way to the keeper
full outside off, leaving the right hander there, left alone
erring in length there, full on the pads and Fulton flicks it away uppishly over midwicket for a boundary
good testing line outside iff, swinging away after pitching, left alone to the keeper who collects it waist-high
short of a good length on the off stump, moves across and defends on the off side
good length on the off stump, driven off the front foot to mid-off
slightly short outside off, steered to point off the back foot
nipping back into the batsman, tries to drive it on the up to mid-off, gets an inside edge onto his pads
end of a good over, short of a length outside off, punched to cover off the back foot
good length on the off stump, gets across to defend on the leg side
short on middle and leg, gets forward and defends it back to the bowler
good length outside off and angling away, Fulton shoulders arms to that one

good length, pitches marginally outside leg stump, and moves into the right hander. Strikes him on his pads as he tries to defend it off the front foot. Looked close, but pitched a fraction outside leg
good length on middle and leg, gets an inside edge wide of deep square leg for a couple
full on the off stump, defended watchfully on the off side
poor ball, ran long hop outside off, rocks on the back foot and pulls it away fiercely over midwicket for a one bounce four
short on the off stump, defended off the back foot to cover
short of a good length outside off, chopped down to short point
shaping away from the right hander, pushed off the back foot wide of cover for a quick single. A wayward throw from Ponting, would have been short of his ground had the throw been accurate
short of a good length outside off, pushed off the back foot to cover
nipping back in, short of a good length on the off stump, punched to cover
dropped on the off side short of point
good length outside off and swinging away from the right hander, defended off the front foot to cover
bang on target, good length on the off stump, defended back to the bowler
a quick offcutter on a good length on the off, guided to point off the front foot
signs of desperation there, Australia have struck early, fullish outside off, tries to slice that over point, gets the elevation but straight to Ferguson at third man
short of a length on middle and off, pushed back to the bowler
straying on the pads, he gets on the back foot and glances it fine to the fine-leg boundary

he's given him! Good length on middle, and held its line this time. Taylor came forward to defend, missed it completely and was struck in line. Correct decision there, Taylor showed his bat to the umpire immediately upon being struck on the pads, but Bucknor is having none of the nonsense
short of a good length outside off, left alone
short of a length outside, guided wide of third man
defended to gully off the back foot
jagged back in, tried to push it back past the bowler, got a thick inside edge onto his pads
good length on the off stump, defended of the front foot to cover
fullish outside off, left alone to the keeper, there was some late away movement for the bowler
pitched on a good length outside leg stump and swung into Fulton, struck on the pads as he tried to work that away on the leg side
Fulton's riding his luck here, good length outside off, he slashes at it hard off the front foot, gets a thick outside edge well wide of slip to the third-man boundary
